article.headline: Smith, Dant, Rubino combine for 58 points
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Khara Smith and Jenni Dant each scored 21 points and Jenna Rubino added 16 points and 14 rebounds to lead No. 19 DePaul to a 118-49 victory over Northwestern on Saturday night.

DePaul's point total narrowly missed the school record of 121 points, scored against Illinois-Chicago in January 1988.

DePaul (4-0) shot 57 percent and outrebounded the Lady Wildcats 53-29.

Caprice Smith added 11 points for DePaul, which led 58-27 at the break.

Northwestern (1-3) got 14 points from Kelly Rae Finley and 13 from Sara Stutz.

The Lady Wildcats were slowed by 27 turnovers and shot just 3-for-15 3-point range.
